Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.68,0:00:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.19,0:00:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.12,0:00:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we will feature the study methods \Nthat are used in Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.39,0:00:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,For a moment, let’s imagine ourselves \Nstarting our day as a Gilead student.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.80,0:00:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.90,0:00:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,See you, Nathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.79,0:00:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a good day in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.79,0:00:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.23,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.23,0:00:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.30,0:00:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.63,0:00:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Nathan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.37,0:00:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lyubomyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.41,0:01:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.14,0:01:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.81,0:01:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I am good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.58,0:01:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How was your night?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.88,0:01:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A long night of studying, \Nbut it was worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.95,0:01:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m really looking forward \Nto the lesson this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.62,0:01:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I agree with you. \NI feel the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.89,0:01:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The information we have been studying \Nis really touching my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.46,0:01:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.76,0:01:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I’ve become \Nmore of a spiritual person,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.73,0:01:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and my relationship with Jehovah \Nhas become so much stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.97,0:01:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning everyone. \NVery good to see you all here this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the study methods \Nthat are helping the students grow
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.17,0:01:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in their relationship with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.61,0:01:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And more importantly, \Nhow can we apply these methods
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.15,0:01:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own personal study?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.38,0:01:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll find the answers and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.72,0:01:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some \Nof the highlights of what’s ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.39,0:01:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,These brothers and sisters describe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.62,0:01:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,how they approach their personal Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re from different parts of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.76,0:01:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but they share \Nmany common study techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.70,0:01:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What questions do they ask \Nas they read and meditate on the Bible?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.70,0:02:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How does their deep study take them \Nbeyond the basics of Bible understanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.97,0:02:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones, \Nare you digging deep into God’s Word now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.88,0:02:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How can this help you \Nmake the truth your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.01,0:02:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And can you succeed even without the support
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.55,0:02:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of those spiritually close to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.78,0:02:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This sister’s experience will show us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.42,0:02:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the benefits of searching the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.76,0:02:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as if for hidden treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.56,0:02:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you be ready to make \Na wise choice in matters of conscience?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.86,0:02:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do study habits affect \Nhow well-prepared and well-trained
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.60,0:02:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your conscience is \Nfor an unexpected situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.30,0:02:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how \Nthe sister in this dramatization
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,answers these questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting for July 2018.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.13,0:03:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin with an archived interview \Nof Brother Allan Boyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Among his many assignments, \NBrother Boyle spent 37 years
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.97,0:03:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Art Department \Nat world headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.74,0:03:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The beautiful and accurate illustrations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.11,0:03:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,produced there enhance our study,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.35,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,helping us to visualize \Nand meditate on what we are reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,An assignment \Nto create these pictures is exciting,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.99,0:03:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but it requires \Nthat a person have spiritual qualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.16,0:03:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Artists collaborate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.16,0:03:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and must humbly listen \Nto each other’s comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.79,0:03:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They must apply direction \Nfrom “the faithful and discreet slave”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.06,0:03:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare artwork \Nthat we can take in as spiritual food.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.50,0:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As you’ll hear Brother Boyle describe,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.84,0:03:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a person must be \Nan avid student of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.51,0:03:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to Brother Boyle’s story,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.74,0:03:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and note what he said was needed \Nfor him to do his assignment well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.63,0:04:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in 1933.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to the age of 18, \Nand one suppertime
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.24,0:04:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother \Nhad invited the company servant,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.34,0:04:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as they were called back then, \Nto come for supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.48,0:04:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked me \Nwhat I was going to do with my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to him, \N“Well, I’m going to pioneer.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.11,0:04:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So three weeks later, \Nat the convention in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.28,0:04:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I got baptized and then \Nwent pioneering six months after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I was 21 when I was in the circuit work,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.69,0:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was a wonderful experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And in those days, \Nof course, you didn’t have a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to have a motorbike.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’d go around \Non the motorbike with my briefcase
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.70,0:04:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and my typewriter \Nand my clothes in the other case on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.94,0:04:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that was very exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.94,0:04:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was invited to go to Gilead, \Nand that was wonderfully exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We had 103 in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.05,0:04:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Little did I know at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.05,0:05:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that I would be sent \Nas a missionary to Ireland.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.86,0:05:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My friend had been invited to go down
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.43,0:05:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to London Bethel to do the artwork there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.03,0:05:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d always wanted to be in Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.20,0:05:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, ‘Well, why don’t I just \Ncall him up and congratulate him?’
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.14,0:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s what I did, \Nand he told me that he decided not to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.57,0:05:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So he said: “If you’re \Nstill interested, why don’t you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.41,0:05:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, call them up and let them know.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.41,0:05:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s what I did. \NThe next morning, I called up London Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and within a week I was \Nin London Bethel doing the graphics work
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.09,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,for the magazines, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a wonderful, thrilling experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.86,0:05:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in London Bethel for a couple of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1977 to 1979,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and then Brother Barry invited me \Nto come over to Brooklyn Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.84,0:06:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that you’re doing \Nsomething that’s going to be beneficial
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.48,0:06:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and helpful to other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.71,0:06:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,even to people in different \Nlanguages, in different cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.82,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A little painting that you do \Nis going to help them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.85,0:06:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to get a memory of something significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.56,0:06:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the most beautiful things \Nabout working in the Art Department
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and doing paintings \Nis that it makes you do research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to investigate. \NIs this the right time of the day?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.83,0:06:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it night? Is it day?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.17,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the sky look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What was it like \Nbefore the Flood when Noah built the ark?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.01,0:06:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he paint underneath the ark?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.71,0:06:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he waterproof it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.35,0:06:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that’s \Nthe most important part, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.35,0:06:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He used bitumen. \NOK, how did he get underneath the ark?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.25,0:06:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he put it on stilts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.89,0:06:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to come up \Nwith all these little questions in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To do the research was very rewarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.52,0:07:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a little model of a boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.96,0:07:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and underneath the deck they used to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a ballast sack of 110 pounds (50 kg) of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It says in the Scriptures \Nthat Jesus was asleep on “a pillow.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.33,0:07:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently, this was \Nthe ballast sack that he was asleep on.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And actually, \Nin the Kingdom Interlinear translation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.70,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t say \Nthat he was asleep on “a pillow”;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it says he was asleep on “the pillow.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.41,0:07:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So apparently, \Nback 2,000 years ago in that area,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.45,0:07:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody knew what “the pillow” was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.59,0:07:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember meeting \Na brother once who’d been to Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.06,0:07:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’d taken a snapshot \Nof somebody’s kitchen in Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.16,0:08:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And to my amazement, on the wall
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.93,0:08:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,—pinned with drawing pins on the wall—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.40,0:08:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was one of the pages of the publications
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.40,0:08:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that we produced here at Brooklyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, remarkably,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.51,0:08:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s wonderful to feel \Nthat whatever we do here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.44,0:08:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—if it’s support work, \Nif it’s the painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.31,0:08:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and, of course, we need \Na lot of support work for the paintings—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all of what we do here
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.22,0:08:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,has an effect upon the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.45,0:08:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,out there in the world, wherever it might be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.76,0:08:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you really feel \Nthat your time is well spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.33,0:08:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re adorning the Word of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.83,0:08:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re helping other people \Nto be taught something from the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is going to be to their benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been very rewarding and thrilling
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.31,0:08:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be in Jehovah’s service, \Nand I’ve really enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Allan Boyle finished \Nhis earthly course in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.07,0:09:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Those in the Art Department \Nwho worked with him
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,remember his enthusiasm \Nand his thorough attention to detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.18,0:09:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What Allan brought to his assignment
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.21,0:09:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,was rooted \Nin his own personal study of the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.52,0:09:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He found it rewarding to do the research
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.92,0:09:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,needed to illustrate Bible scenes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.66,0:09:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the Writing Department supplies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.16,0:09:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a team of researchers to assist the artists.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.36,0:09:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you recall \Nwhat Allan said helped his research?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked questions \Nabout the scenes he was painting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.17,0:09:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,These same kinds of questions \Nare part of the study methods
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.61,0:09:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilead students learn in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.84,0:09:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the same methods \Nthat we’ll learn about in this program.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.05,0:10:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.05,0:10:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,if you received an invitation
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.05,0:10:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend the next class of Gilead School?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.19,0:10:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For many, it has been \Na lifelong dream to attend Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.82,0:10:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The course helps students \Nkeep “a tight grip on the word of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.03,0:10:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For others, the idea of five months \Nof intense study seems intimidating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.03,0:10:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We know we need to study,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.40,0:10:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but we may find \Nit a challenge to get the most
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.97,0:10:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the time we spend \Nreading God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.58,0:10:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,In this program, we will discuss \Nwhy study is so important,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.58,0:10:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,what it means to study something,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.65,0:10:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and how you can get more \Nfrom your study sessions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.45,0:10:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Since most cannot attend Gilead,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.82,0:10:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we will demonstrate \Nthe method used in Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.56,0:10:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,First, why is study so important?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.27,0:10:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Only by study can we \Nkeep “a tight grip on the word of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.20,0:10:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When the apostle Paul penned these words,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.91,0:11:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,he was imprisoned and nearing the end \Nof his action-packed life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.28,0:11:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He had been the “apostle to the nations”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.65,0:11:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and had spent his best years
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.38,0:11:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,taking the Word of God \Nto the then-known world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As he reflected on the fruits of his labors,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.86,0:11:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrote a letter to his friends \Nin the congregation in Philippi in Macedonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.69,0:11:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspired by holy spirit, he wrote words
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.70,0:11:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that would aid his brothers \Nto gain the prize of eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.70,0:11:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,These words are found \Nat Philippians 2:15, 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.61,0:11:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read them:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“So that you may come to be \Nblameless and innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“children of God \Nwithout a blemish in the midst
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.78,0:11:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“of a crooked and twisted generation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.35,0:11:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“among whom you are shining \Nas illuminators in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.99,0:11:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,keeping a tight grip on the word of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.39,0:11:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the joy Paul felt
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.16,0:11:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was reunited \Nin the heavenly resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.33,0:12:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with those who listened to his admonition
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep “a tight grip on the word of life”!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we have \Nthe heavenly or earthly hope,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.04,0:12:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul’s words can help us gain \Nthe prize of eternal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.98,0:12:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,They imprint on our hearts and minds \Na basic exhortation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.05,0:12:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that will lead us through these last days \Nand into our everlasting reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.06,0:12:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is, Will we remain \N‘blameless and without blemish
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.06,0:12:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the midst of this crooked \Nand twisted generation’ of our day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.63,0:12:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we rejoice with other faithful servants \Nof God in the new world?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.64,0:12:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We can and we will
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.41,0:12:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,if we take to heart Paul’s counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.61,0:12:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep “a tight grip on the word of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, what does it mean to study?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.45,0:12:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop and contemplate this word picture
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.82,0:12:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,for keeping a tight grip.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.26,0:12:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine a hiker who has slipped near a ledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.49,0:13:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But before falling over the cliff, \Nhe grabs hold of a tree branch.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,How tight do you think \Nhis grip will be on that branch?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.90,0:13:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a halfhearted effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.50,0:13:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, keeping a tight grip \Non the word of life
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.81,0:13:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is not just a mechanical routine, \Nnor is it a casual habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.81,0:13:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It requires strenuous effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.68,0:13:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It involves actively living \Nby the truths in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.69,0:13:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To do this, we must understand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.36,0:13:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,more than what God \Nexpressly commands and condemns.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.89,0:13:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We must be able to identify principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.76,0:13:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or life lessons, contained in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Once identified, we must understand
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.20,0:13:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,how to match these valuable truths
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.71,0:13:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to specific situations in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.14,0:13:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we must allow these principles \Nto influence our decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.25,0:13:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and guide our reaction \Nto trials and temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.35,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ask yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How strong is my grip \Non the word of life?’
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.53,0:14:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To answer that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.53,0:14:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s consider \Nthe fundamentals of Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.53,0:14:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not about old methods or new methods,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,nor is it about what device you are using.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This discussion transcends devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.01,0:14:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Study requires active thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.34,0:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In a world of increasing distractions,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.38,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this is becoming an even greater challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.25,0:14:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve often received instant information
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that enables us to quickly recite facts,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is not the same as active thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.33,0:14:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Through active thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.33,0:14:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we draw meaningful conclusions in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.43,0:14:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We are certainly grateful \Nfor all the study tools we’ve been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We should use these to the full.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.34,0:14:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, we need to be careful
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.08,0:14:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that these tools do not cause us \Nto develop mental laziness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.95,0:15:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Devices can help us to access information,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.22,0:15:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but they can’t think for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.05,0:15:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We must work hard if we are \Nto develop new patterns of thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.56,0:15:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, if we study \NThe Watchtower on a device,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.23,0:15:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we can use the hyperlink feature \Nto read the Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.30,0:15:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With a simple touch, \Nwe quickly find and read the verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.14,0:15:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.14,0:15:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you regularly do this, \Nyou get a grip on the word of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But would you like to get \Na tight grip on the word of life?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.51,0:15:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To get a tight grip requires more effort
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.38,0:15:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,than a swipe of a finger \Nand then swiftly moving on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.46,0:15:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to slow down \Nand analyze the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.79,0:15:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then will the information you study
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.90,0:15:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,become imprinted on your mind and heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.70,0:15:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving a clear and distinct impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How, then, can I get more out of my study?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.54,0:16:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s demonstrate a method \Ntaught during Gilead School.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.81,0:16:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It involves the use of six questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.01,0:16:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The following poem, written \Nby English journalist Rudyard Kipling,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,can help guide better thinking:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.45,0:16:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“I keep six honest serving-men
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.79,0:16:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“(They taught me all I knew);
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.96,0:16:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Their names are What and Why
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.86,0:16:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“and When and How
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and Where and Who.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.60,0:16:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When studying God’s Word, \Nask yourself these questions
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.54,0:16:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and then do research in our publications
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the facts \Nand discern the spiritual lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.75,0:16:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To illustrate how to do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.01,0:16:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s open our Bibles to Genesis chapter 49
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and look at verses 22 through 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.49,0:16:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we ask the when and where.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.16,0:16:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, with some research,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.27,0:17:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,we learn that Jacob \Nspoke these words near the end of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.77,0:17:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in Egypt,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.77,0:17:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but what he described \Ntakes us back to Canaan some 40 years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.54,0:17:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,when his son Joseph was a young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.21,0:17:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we have \Na clearer picture of these verses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.62,0:17:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So now, let’s read and analyze verse 22:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.05,0:17:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Joseph is the offshoot of a fruitful tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.06,0:17:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a fruitful tree by a spring, \Nwhose branches extend over the wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.40,0:17:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“The offshoot of a fruitful tree.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.17,0:17:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the “fruitful tree”?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.90,0:17:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It is Joseph’s father, Jacob.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.44,0:17:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,How was he fruitful?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.81,0:17:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He bore many children.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.18,0:17:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s “branches extend over the wall.”
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.65,0:17:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jacob’s offshoot, \NJoseph is singled out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.32,0:17:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for a special blessing \Nsuperior to that of his brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.65,0:17:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.66,0:17:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph proved he had \Nthe qualities needed for leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.46,0:18:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,However, of even greater value \Nthan his abilities
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.63,0:18:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was his being a spiritual man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.70,0:18:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 23:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.17,0:18:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the archers kept harassing him
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.40,0:18:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and shot at him and kept harboring \Nanimosity against him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.58,0:18:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“The archers kept harassing him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.98,0:18:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are “the archers”?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.98,0:18:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s half brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.98,0:18:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.12,0:18:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They shot figuratively at Joseph
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.29,0:18:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,—arrows of envy and hatred \Nand jealousy were used to attack him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.26,0:18:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, eventually, \Nhis brothers sold him into slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.36,0:18:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s read verse 24:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.93,0:18:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“And yet his bow remained in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.00,0:18:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“and his hands stayed strong and agile.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.37,0:18:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“This was from the hands \Nof the powerful one of Jacob,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.74,0:18:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,from the shepherd, the stone of Israel.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.61,0:18:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“His bow remained in place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.95,0:18:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.45,0:18:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite the repeated attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.45,0:18:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph repaid animosity with kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph endured this ill-treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.29,0:19:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and did not weaken in his devotion to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.46,0:19:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we ask, How?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that Joseph \Nkept a spiritual outlook
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,despite the harassment and animosity?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.63,0:19:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read verse 25:
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.24,0:19:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“He [Joseph] is from the God of your father,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.31,0:19:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will help you, \Nand he is with the Almighty,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.31,0:19:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will bless you with the blessings \Nof the heavens above,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.41,0:19:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“with the blessings of the deep below,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.78,0:19:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with the blessings of the breasts and womb.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.85,0:19:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“He is with the Almighty.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.42,0:19:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph had Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.56,0:19:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Almighty was by his side through it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.96,0:19:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve used our questions \Nto get the facts of the account,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.67,0:19:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re not done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s use them \Nto take our study to a spiritual plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.84,0:19:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, let’s ask a what question.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.41,0:19:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this account \Nteach us about Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:20:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah never abandons his loyal servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.98,0:20:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the depths of prison, \NJoseph was not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.15,0:20:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah found ways to bless Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now make the connection \Nto Jehovah’s people today,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.76,0:20:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,including yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.80,0:20:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will never abandon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, he shows loyal love \Nto all those who serve him whole-souled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.97,0:20:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jehovah let Joseph \Nremain in prison indefinitely?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.98,0:20:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.98,0:20:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At the appointed time, relief came.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.98,0:20:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph was raised from a prisoner in chains
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.78,0:20:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the second most powerful man in Egypt
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.02,0:20:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—from prison to palace in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.16,0:20:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Make the connection to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.69,0:20:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trials are temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will soon bring relief,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,even in unexpected or surprising ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.07,0:20:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, we are never alone;
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, let’s ask the question, How?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the account \Ncontribute to the Bible’s theme?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.15,0:21:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph suffered, but his suffering led
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.45,0:21:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to the survival of Abraham’s offspring,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.26,0:21:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,leading to the Messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.66,0:21:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s account \Nis not just a riveting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.29,0:21:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It directly contributed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.30,0:21:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to the development of Jehovah’s purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.83,0:21:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about this:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.97,0:21:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In spite of the poor conduct of his brothers,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.44,0:21:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph forgave them and took the initiative
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.91,0:21:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to improve their relationship with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.25,0:21:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s attitude \Nwas a reflection of Jehovah’s attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.25,0:21:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,With their family reunited,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah also forgave Joseph’s brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.52,0:21:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and took the initiative \Nin restoring their relationship with Himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.53,0:21:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jehovah gave Joseph’s brother Judah
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.53,0:22:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the honor of being \Nan ancestor of the Messiah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.74,0:22:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the lessons in this account?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.21,0:22:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s highlight just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.48,0:22:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Genesis 49:23:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.81,0:22:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“But the archers kept harassing him
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.85,0:22:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and shot at him and kept harboring \Nanimosity against him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.25,0:22:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Arrows of animosity were fired at Joseph.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall Joseph’s response in verse 24?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.10,0:22:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“And yet his bow remained in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.10,0:22:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and his hands stayed strong and agile.”
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.97,0:22:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, he did not return fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.31,0:22:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,His bow remained in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.91,0:22:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflect on the last time \Nyou were wronged by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.28,0:22:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How did we react to what we experienced?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.12,0:22:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we seek to vindicate ourselves \Nor insist on our rights?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.26,0:22:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we fire arrows of animosity in return,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.06,0:23:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or did we show mercy and loyal love?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.83,0:23:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Did our reaction reveal \Nthat God’s spirit was operative on us?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.73,0:23:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Joseph, we know \Nwe will have Jehovah’s approval
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.81,0:23:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we are wronged or experience trials
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.11,0:23:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that make us feel like we are in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.98,0:23:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflective questions like these
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.65,0:23:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,enable us to make the account our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.28,0:23:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes part of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.09,0:23:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,part of our way of thinking, \Nour way of acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.62,0:23:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This nourishes our relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This type of study rewards us \Nnot simply with a collection of facts
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.40,0:23:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that impress us today \Nand are forgotten tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.37,0:23:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, it leaves us \Nwith core principles that we remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.54,0:23:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that influence our decisions, \Nand that guide our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.58,0:23:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We tighten our grip on the word of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.48,0:23:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s review the fundamentals of study.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.22,0:23:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, this is not \Nabout old methods or new methods
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.35,0:24:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or about what device you are using.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This discussion transcends devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.79,0:24:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s about basic methods of Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.53,0:24:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We can liken these three phases of study
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.37,0:24:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to gathering, sifting, and baking grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.47,0:24:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Gathering is when we read the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.41,0:24:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t run through the field \Ngrabbing just handfuls of grain;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,we systematically harvest the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.11,0:24:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sifting is when we sort out what we gathered,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.28,0:24:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,answering who, what, where, \Nwhen, why, and how to get the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.96,0:24:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Baking is when we think
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.53,0:24:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,—“turning up the heat” in our mind and heart—
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.56,0:24:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,something no one else can do for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.06,0:24:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The questions we ask \Ncan take our study to a spiritual plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.80,0:24:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Most importantly, \Nwhat does this teach me about Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.81,0:24:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it contribute to the Bible’s theme?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.91,0:25:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the bottom line: \NWhat is the lesson for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.12,0:25:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gave us a mind \Nthat is begging to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.56,0:25:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a gift with the capacity \Nto cultivate thinking ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.29,0:25:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When we make the effort \Nto unearth gems from God’s Word,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.83,0:25:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we find that study \Nis rewarding and delightful.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.20,0:25:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, our study skills enable us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.40,0:25:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep a tight grip on the word of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.57,0:25:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A tight grip on God’s Word \Nwill make our life better now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.21,0:25:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and give us the opportunity \Nto continue learning
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.28,0:25:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,about our heavenly Father for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.95,0:25:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Joseph’s account \Nwas an excellent example for us
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.62,0:25:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to demonstrate \Nthe fundamentals of Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.36,0:25:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,During our discussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.36,0:25:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we used pictures \Nto help bring the account to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.27,0:25:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As we learned \Nfrom Brother Boyle’s interview,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.94,0:25:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,pictures and illustrations \Ngive us an accurate image
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.34,0:25:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to use in our meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.54,0:26:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And if there’s a video,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.64,0:26:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,we have yet another way \Nto imagine ourselves in the account.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.98,0:26:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re excited \Nto introduce this month’s music video
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.78,0:26:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,depicting the trials \Nand blessings that Joseph experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.89,0:26:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It reminds us that, like Joseph,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.59,0:26:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when we have Jehovah, \Nwe are never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.08,0:26:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandoned and betrayed, \NForsaken and alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.29,0:27:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Despair my one companion, \NMy heart within me like a stone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.37,0:27:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,With no one here for me, \NNo kindly word of care,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.49,0:27:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’ll offer consolation? \NMy heavy burden, who can share?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.86,0:27:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not alone; \NI never was.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.01,0:27:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never be, \NAnd all because
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.15,0:27:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows; \NJehovah sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.22,0:27:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He hears my prayer; \NHe’s here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.23,0:28:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever comes my way, \NI’m never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.88,0:28:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I may lose \NBy sticking close to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.22,0:28:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter who may fail me, \NI know you’ll never be untrue.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.14,0:28:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re close to me, O God, \NAnd never far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.15,0:29:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My faith, my hope, reliance​— \NI know you never will betray.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.76,0:29:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not alone; \NI never was.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.80,0:29:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never be, \NAnd all because
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.01,0:29:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows; \NJehovah sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.85,0:29:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He hears my prayer; \NHe’s here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.13,0:29:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever comes my way, \NI’m never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.17,0:29:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I never was.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.77,0:29:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll never be, \NAnd all because
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.18,0:30:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knows; \NJehovah sees.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.39,0:30:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He hears my prayer; \NHe’s here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.29,0:30:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever comes my way, \NI’m never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.98,0:30:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt as Joseph did?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.08,0:30:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There were times when Joseph’s life \Nwas not turning out as he had hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.69,0:30:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He no doubt wondered \Nif he’d ever be set free from prison
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.26,0:30:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,or if he’d ever see his father again \Nor his younger brother, Benjamin.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.03,0:30:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But Joseph knew that his God, Jehovah, \Nnever lost sight of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.04,0:30:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This surely helped him endure.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.01,0:31:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We could be in a painful situation \Nthat seems to drag on endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.61,0:31:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But when we study \Na Bible account like Joseph’s
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—asking the six questions—
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.65,0:31:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we can fully understand \Nand apply the lessons in our life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.75,0:31:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we can build the same faith that he had
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.79,0:31:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we too are never alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.46,0:31:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s now listen to brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.56,0:31:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,who are using \Nthe study methods we’ve discussed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.67,0:31:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Some learned them in Gilead School, \Nothers from Gilead graduates,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.74,0:31:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,or good examples \Nin their families and congregations.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.77,0:31:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve also applied what they learned
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.78,0:31:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,from our publications \Nabout good study habits.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.55,0:31:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,See if any of the ways they study
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.65,0:31:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,could help you keep \N“a tight grip” on God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.55,0:31:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you study,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.39,0:31:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you understand Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.39,0:31:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you understand Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.43,0:31:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.09,0:31:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah clearly tells us:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.93,0:31:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“My thoughts are not your thoughts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.97,0:31:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we want to understand \NJehovah’s thinking better,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.13,0:32:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to dig deep in our study,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.60,0:32:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we share those thoughts with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.61,0:32:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal study is like fuel
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.64,0:32:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that keeps you going.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.65,0:32:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Personally, I’m not a good student,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.95,0:32:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but I really learned how to study the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.12,0:32:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible came alive during Gilead.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.62,0:32:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-discipline is involved \N—very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.33,0:32:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I overcome the tiredness aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.80,0:32:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Bible study by not doing it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.00,0:32:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time of day \Nwhen I know I’m going to be tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.27,0:32:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be tired for other things later on \N—but not for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.17,0:32:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Each session of my Bible study \Nbegins with a prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.01,0:32:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“Please help me recognize \Nit is counsel for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.08,0:32:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and then give me the strength \Nto work on it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.92,0:32:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a color-coded system,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.29,0:32:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,so I know what certain things stand for.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.92,0:32:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a particular color
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.86,0:33:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s good hand in people’s lives;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.86,0:33:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I have another color for warning examples;
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.34,0:33:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have another for fine examples to imitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.69,0:33:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to get behind the information,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.32,0:33:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not just focus on one verse or one chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.96,0:33:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,See who’s involved, the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.63,0:33:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the conditions, how many people are there,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.86,0:33:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you’ll get \Nthe true meaning of the verse.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.17,0:33:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,John 1:1,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.17,0:33:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,who is “the Word”?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.07,0:33:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We can go to verse 18.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.51,0:33:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Begotten” meant
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.34,0:33:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he had a beginning, \Na time when he started
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.98,0:33:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,—when he began—
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.35,0:33:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in heaven with his Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.55,0:33:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s where he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.72,0:34:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Philippians 4:6, 7 is a scripture \Nthat I’ve read many times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.99,0:34:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“The peace of God that excels all thought.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.43,0:34:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, how do you get that?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.43,0:34:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s from having \Na good relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.57,0:34:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that God’s peace \N‘guards your heart’?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.34,0:34:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“By means of Christ Jesus” our Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.91,0:34:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said: “Why by Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.74,0:34:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Because Jesus paid the ransom;
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.11,0:34:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that ransom is what makes possible \Na relationship with Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.22,0:34:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So it almost goes full circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.48,0:35:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I attended a School for Congregation Elders
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.55,0:35:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that had Gilead graduates as instructors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.72,0:35:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the methods is to analyze
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.66,0:35:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain Bible account \Nfrom different perspectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.89,0:35:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t see \Nthe whole picture from one angle.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.76,0:35:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I share my research results \Nwith Bible students,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.90,0:35:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and that helps them \Nto know Jehovah better,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.13,0:35:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and it helps them to see \Nthat what they’re studying
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.47,0:35:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is of practical value.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.01,0:35:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I had studied up on Jacob;
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.68,0:35:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he wrestled all night
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.98,0:35:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.31,0:35:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to share it \Nwith some of my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.85,0:35:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the brothers \Nthat happened to sit around
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.35,0:35:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,when this discussion was going on \Ncame back to me, and he said to me:
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.29,0:35:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“I had concluded my arrangements
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.13,0:35:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“to quit full-time service.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.70,0:35:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“But after listening to that discussion,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.50,0:35:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve decided that I’m no longer stopping.”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.54,0:36:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was \Nsuch a wonderful moment for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.64,0:36:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I thanked Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.55,0:36:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When I learned that I \Nwas going to become a mom,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.71,0:36:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, “Jehovah, if this little one
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.82,0:36:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,could love you, \Nthen I’ll get to keep him forever.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.49,0:36:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And I began to teach everything \NI was learning to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.49,0:36:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s a matter
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.89,0:36:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of keeping my faith strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.06,0:36:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and there’s no shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.67,0:36:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Every session of study \Nthat is properly done with good meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.40,0:36:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,adds a new pillar
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.40,0:36:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to the strength of our faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.58,0:36:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to those times \Nwhen I can, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.94,0:36:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,run upstairs by myself \Nand just shut everything off,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.85,0:36:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s just me and Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.09,0:36:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Life today is very unpredictable,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.39,0:36:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’ve come to see that as long as I \Nkeep a tight grip on God’s Word,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.42,0:36:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,nothing can “separate [me] from God’s love.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.90,0:36:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The joy these brothers and sisters get \Nfrom their personal study
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.53,0:37:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is clearly heard in their expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.97,0:37:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall what they said:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.97,0:37:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“The more you understand Jehovah, \Nthe more you love him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.21,0:37:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Study is like fuel that keeps you going.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.41,0:37:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And “I can shut everything off, \Nand it’s just me and Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.12,0:37:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We also heard them ask the six questions:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.88,0:37:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who, what, where, when, why, and how.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.15,0:37:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They also used tools for research \Nand note-taking that works for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.33,0:37:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something you saw \Nor that we discussed
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.33,0:37:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’d like to add \Nto your study routine?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.76,0:37:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, try it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.07,0:37:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones, it’s true \Nthat the more you understand Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.74,0:37:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you love him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.87,0:37:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a blessing you have \Nif your family worships Jehovah with you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.74,0:37:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and teaches you how to draw close to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.91,0:37:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But some young ones \Nhave had to build their faith
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.65,0:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without their family’s support.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.52,0:37:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to the experience of Ersi Royer \Nfrom the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.59,0:38:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What spiritual decision did she face \Nat just 14 years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.09,0:38:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And what did she do \Nthat illustrates the value
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.03,0:38:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of deep personal study?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.93,0:38:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing up,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.57,0:38:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn’t the typical,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.57,0:38:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“My mom is a pioneer, my dad is an elder,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.17,0:38:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re doing great in the congregation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.51,0:38:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My family life wasn’t the best,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.35,0:38:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so why would I want to do this religion \Nthat nobody is happy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.42,0:38:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,in our family with?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.02,0:38:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think that can make you feel
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.52,0:38:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,very alone or odd
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.36,0:38:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,or awkward or secluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.23,0:38:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that time, \NI was graduating eighth grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.33,0:38:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There were dances;
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.90,0:38:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,friends were hanging out, going to parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.87,0:38:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember thinking: \N‘Wow, these look like really nice kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.54,0:38:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren’t I doing that?’
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.38,0:38:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I hadn’t really delved into the Bible enough \Nto answer questions
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.38,0:38:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that I really needed to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.62,0:38:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I went in prayer to Jehovah and said: \N“I’m so sorry, but today I’m not a Witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.42,0:39:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to try to prove \Neverything that I’ve been taught is wrong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.09,0:39:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him that if he’s real,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.83,0:39:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to help me understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.43,0:39:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went in my room
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.30,0:39:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and shut the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.90,0:39:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I got every book off the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.00,0:39:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I started off organized,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.14,0:39:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but by the end of the evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.47,0:39:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I had books \Nall over the place with pages open.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.24,0:39:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The more I kept reading about Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.68,0:39:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the more the next topic would take me \Nto then connect the scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.51,0:39:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus is linked to Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.45,0:39:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the angels are linked to Jehovah; \Nthe resurrection is linked to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.52,0:39:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can’t believe in one thing \Nand not everything else
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.49,0:39:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if you really want to know the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.69,0:39:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that’s what did it for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.03,0:39:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the scripture in Psalms
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.30,0:39:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when it said \Nthat ‘you saw even the embryo of me.’
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.94,0:39:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And it was an emotional scripture for me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.94,0:39:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because I thought: \N‘Wow,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.64,0:39:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,‘my parents aren’t doing great \Nin the truth right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.71,0:39:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,‘But Jehovah found a way to find me,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.11,0:40:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and he knew what I could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.95,0:40:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Now I have my answer. \NI don’t have an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.88,0:40:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Jehovah gave me enough knowledge \Nthat now I’m responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.72,0:40:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I now need to act on that \Nand show my love in return for him.’
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.83,0:40:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Within a week, I found another sister
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.36,0:40:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,in the hall that was really helpful \Nin me getting out
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.86,0:40:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in service quite often.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.03,0:40:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t think to this day she ever knew \Nhow much I appreciated that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.40,0:40:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Although things were declining \Nin our family spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.61,0:40:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to get baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.84,0:40:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,As I progressed spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.85,0:40:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see that I did not have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.85,0:40:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the support of my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.02,0:40:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but I had to trust that Jehovah \Nwould help me through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.59,0:40:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And at least by the time I got home, \Nif there was an issue,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.35,0:40:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the strength of the meeting \Nand the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.36,0:40:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and joy that they \Ncouldn’t take away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.40,0:40:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I came home one day \Nwith some friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.76,0:40:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a nice day
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.50,0:40:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,—encouraging, upbuilding.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.37,0:40:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We pulled into our driveway; \Nthey dropped me off
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.67,0:40:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and said good-bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.27,0:41:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents were really upset
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.11,0:41:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,when they came and met me at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.48,0:41:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They couldn’t fully understand
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.18,0:41:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,why I was making my decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.89,0:41:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I was \Nto serve Jehovah more fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.16,0:41:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We just could not agree
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.16,0:41:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on where my relationship \Nwith Jehovah was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.86,0:41:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that point, \NI left with the clothes on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.67,0:41:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,In a matter of a few minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.34,0:41:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,my life forever changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.78,0:41:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a spiritual aunt that took me in,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.15,0:41:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me gather myself together,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.88,0:41:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and literally fed me, clothed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.66,0:41:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.06,0:41:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so then, my support became Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.29,0:41:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.16,0:42:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that a sister told me years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.10,0:42:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“Be who you needed when you were young.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.80,0:42:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when I look at those little ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.31,0:42:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I look at myself and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.08,0:42:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How could I have benefited
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,from someone taking the time for me \Nwhen I was that age?’
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.18,0:42:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve always tried remembering the young ones
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.18,0:42:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,—because that’s just part of who I am—
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.09,0:42:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and making sure that they know \Nthat they’re not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.99,0:42:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If there is a young one out there \Nwho isn’t sure
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.46,0:42:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if this is the truth or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.86,0:42:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like them to know \Nthat Jehovah knows
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.76,0:42:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,who they are,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.60,0:42:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s finding a way \Nfor them to know him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.47,0:42:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is real, \Nhe knows them by name,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.47,0:42:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,he wants them to live, \Nand he’s fighting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.65,0:42:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,How amazing that young Ersi chose \Nto spend an entire day studying
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.65,0:42:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,—proving to herself \Nthat Jehovah knew her and loved her.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.15,0:42:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But this was no onetime study marathon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.12,0:43:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,From there, she worked to develop \Nthe study habits she needed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.89,0:43:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to endure, grow, \Nand become a spiritual person.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.67,0:43:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,She pioneered for several years,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.97,0:43:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and now serves at Bethel \Nwith her husband, Jeff.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.97,0:43:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In my conversation with Ersi, \Nshe expressed her love for her family
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.68,0:43:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hope that someday in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.24,0:43:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,she’ll be reunited with them spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.48,0:43:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no situation in life
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.55,0:43:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be handled better than by seeking
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.25,0:43:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s guidance in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.16,0:43:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s certainly true \Nin matters of conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.33,0:43:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In these situations,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.33,0:43:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah does not tell us \Nwhat to do with a command,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.30,0:43:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but his Word gives us the principles \Nwe use to train our conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.34,0:43:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.47,0:43:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma has to make a difficult decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.34,0:43:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,How is her conscience involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.61,0:43:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and what steps \Ndoes she take to make her decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.38,0:43:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day we make choices
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.39,0:44:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that can affect \Nour relationship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.72,0:44:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When there’s a clear Scriptural command,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.73,0:44:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the right choice may seem easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.46,0:44:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if there’s not?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.17,0:44:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we be sure \Nwe’re making a wise decision?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.67,0:44:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,An invitation to our niece’s wedding arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.18,0:44:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas was excited about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.02,0:44:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I was excited too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.62,0:44:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But the ceremony
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.69,0:44:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was being held at a local church.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.26,0:44:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wondered if it would still be OK \Nfor me to attend.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.10,0:44:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Thomas wasn’t yet willing
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.10,0:44:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to accept a Bible study, \Nhe gradually softened over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.87,0:44:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,since I came into the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.11,0:44:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he understood why \NI would never enter a church for worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.28,0:44:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but what about attending a wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.85,0:45:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah approves of weddings.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.18,0:45:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.79,0:45:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I went to help Amy plan a menu
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.85,0:45:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,for the pioneer school lunch coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.63,0:45:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She noticed I was a bit distracted,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.53,0:45:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,so I told her my concerns about the wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.23,0:45:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’re not thinking of going, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.00,0:45:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy sure had a strong opinion on the matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.74,0:45:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t feel \Nshe really understood my situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.75,0:45:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Although I appreciated her concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.21,0:45:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like she was judging me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.25,0:45:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, I decided \Nto visit Charlotte and Allan
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.22,0:45:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask their advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.36,0:45:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like me, Charlotte had come into the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.00,0:45:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,many years before Allan, \Nso they really understood my situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.93,0:45:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Amy right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.94,0:45:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it be wrong to attend the wedding?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.57,0:46:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do if you were me?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.91,0:46:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlotte explained that in situations
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.21,0:46:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where there’s no specific Bible command,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.88,0:46:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes a matter of conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.22,0:46:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And what one person’s conscience allows
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.29,0:46:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,may be different from another.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.09,0:46:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.06,0:46:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we make decisions \Nthat leave us with a good conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.18,0:46:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But how do I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.25,0:46:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dear Emma, it’s really a matter of training.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.05,0:46:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Allan showed me the scripture \Nat Hebrews 5:14,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.99,0:46:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,where the apostle Paul wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.99,0:46:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“Solid food belongs to mature people,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.59,0:46:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“to those who through use
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.59,0:46:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“have their powers of discernment trained
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.13,0:46:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to distinguish both right and wrong.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.83,0:47:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But Paul didn’t just write those words;
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.07,0:47:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he lived them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.41,0:47:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He carefully studied \Nthe principles in God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.58,0:47:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result, \Nhe was able to make decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.02,0:47:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that left him with a good conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.32,0:47:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So even when there’s no stated law \Non a matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.79,0:47:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we can always find a Bible principle
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.03,0:47:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that can give us insight into God’s thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.27,0:47:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I made it a matter of prayer, \Nand then I got to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.31,0:47:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I researched articles
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.22,0:47:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Watch Tower Publications Index \Nand the Research Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.35,0:47:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I found a really good thought \Nin chapter 2 of the “God’s Love” book.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.03,0:48:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I also read about others \Nwho faced similar situations
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.40,0:48:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and what Bible principles they found helpful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.47,0:48:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I meditated on all these.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.55,0:48:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As I kept studying, \NI was able to bring my conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.32,0:48:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in harmony with Jehovah’s spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.22,0:48:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,not just with my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.23,0:48:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that having \Na Bible-trained conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.60,0:48:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn’t mean everyone \Nwill always think exactly alike
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.91,0:48:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—and that’s OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.94,0:48:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we train our conscience \Nby applying Bible principles,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.21,0:48:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,it will guide us along in life, \Nso that each of us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.12,0:48:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,can remain in God’s love.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.92,0:49:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What did our sister, Emma, \Ndo that we can imitate?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.22,0:49:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When she realized \Nthat she needed more information,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.96,0:49:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,she got to work!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.76,0:49:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She studied in order \Nto train her conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.57,0:49:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and to make a decision \Nthat left her conscience clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.40,0:49:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do the same \Nwhen a conscience matter comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.54,0:49:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.57,0:49:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We can prepare in advance,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.68,0:49:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,train our conscience on matters \Nthat do not have clear Bible commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.41,0:49:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and study Bible principles
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.62,0:49:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that teach our conscience \Nthe rules it should work with.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.22,0:49:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, when we need it, it’s ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.39,0:49:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We can trust it and make decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.86,0:49:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,in harmony with a Bible-trained conscience.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.90,0:49:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We urge you brothers and sisters:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.10,0:49:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep “a tight grip on the word of life.”
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.67,0:49:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what our program has been about.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.34,0:49:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned why \Nit’s essential to stay close to God
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.17,0:49:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and to receive his gift of everlasting life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.88,0:50:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But what’s more, \Nwe learned practical ways to do it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.21,0:50:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,using tried and true methods \Nof personal Bible study.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.85,0:50:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not have \Nan opportunity to attend Gilead
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.02,0:50:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or another theocratic school,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.32,0:50:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah shows all of us \Nhow to benefit from his written Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.26,0:50:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What an expression of God’s love!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.63,0:50:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To prepare this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.84,0:50:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,our team spent time \Nwith the Theocratic Schools Department
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.31,0:50:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,at the world headquarters facility \Nin Patterson, New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.98,0:50:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This has been the home \Nfor Gilead School since 1995.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.28,0:50:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And since arriving here,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.32,0:50:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,47 classes have graduated.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.99,0:50:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Gilead School began \Nwith its first class in 1943,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.96,0:50:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and since then, \Nclose to 9,000 students have been trained.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.96,0:50:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When students come to class each day,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.20,0:50:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,the writings and models on display
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.97,0:50:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,put their mind on spiritual things
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.74,0:50:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,as they get ready to study God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.47,0:51:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 11:9 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.91,0:51:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“The earth will certainly be filled \Nwith the knowledge of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.08,0:51:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as the waters cover the sea.”
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.08,0:51:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our worldwide brotherhood
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.82,0:51:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,works in harmony with that prophecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.75,0:51:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s fitting then that here in the classroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.96,0:51:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,lectures cover every part of the Bible,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.03,0:51:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,exploring background information
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.09,0:51:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the sense of the account.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.46,0:51:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . probably still got bruises.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.90,0:51:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And Paul is telling them, very honestly,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.64,0:51:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,‘we have to enter through many tribulations.’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.07,0:51:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine, you’re sitting there \Nand you’re looking at this man
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.21,0:51:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,bruised and cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.21,0:51:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.21,0:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We (you and I) \Nhave to go through many tribulations.’
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.52,0:51:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Students participate freely,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.29,0:51:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,drawing lessons that they can use \Nin their life and assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.69,0:51:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It impresses me to see \Nthat the Christian congregation in our time
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.59,0:51:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,follows exactly \Nthe pattern that was used back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.50,0:52:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Studying in the Theocratic Schools’ library
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.37,0:52:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,is a cherished part of their day.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.17,0:52:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In a quiet, relaxed setting,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.17,0:52:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,they associate figuratively \Nwith “the faithful and discreet slave,”
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.71,0:52:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,searching and taking in the spiritual food
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.18,0:52:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that nourishes \Nand strengthens their relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.75,0:52:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with their heavenly Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.89,0:52:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Students benefit from the hard work \Nof the school instructors.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.12,0:52:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the direction \Nof the Teaching Committee
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.26,0:52:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.33,0:52:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,they manage the curriculum \Nfor Gilead and other schools
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.13,0:52:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that are taught here and in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.23,0:52:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Through their diligent efforts \Nand Jehovah’s blessing,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.87,0:52:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the Theocratic Schools staff \Ncount it a privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.14,0:52:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve their brothers \Nand the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.38,0:52:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We send you \Nour sincere Christian love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.82,0:52:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for joining us this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.45,0:52:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.62,0:52:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
